"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-06-07-Wang-Chuqin-ready-to-build-his-era-at-2024-Summer-Olympic-Games-1uerHSPrZPq-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Wang Chuqin of China looks on in the men's singles final at the World Table Tennis Chongqing Champions in southwest China's Chongqing Municipality, June 3, 2024. /CFP  Wang Chuqin of China will participate in three table tennis events at the upcoming 2024 Summer Olympic Games in Paris: the men's singles, the men's doubles and the mixed doubles competitions.  Three years ago, Wang was with the Chinese national team at the Tokyo Olympic Games, but served as a substitute. His main duty was helping teammates during practice. While watching his compatriots win four of the sport's five gold medals, he was also wondering when he would get the chance to play himself.  \\\"Though I was in the stands watching the Chinese national flag fly for my teammates, I was no less excited,\\\" Wang told China Media Group (CMG). \\\"I was so happy about the honor they achieved and proud of them. I wanted to be like them.\\\"  Wang did not have to wait too long to receive his opportunity. In 2022, he won nine titles in total, including four in singles competition. Over the following year, he further improved his performance by becoming the first table tennis player to win four golds at the 19th Asian Games in Hangzhou, east China's Zhejiang Province.  Wang Chuqin of China competes in the men's singles final against Fan Zhendong of China at the World Table Tennis Chongqing Champions in southwest China's Chongqing Municipality, June 3, 2024. /CFP  In July 2023, Wang moved to the No. 1 spot in men's singles in the World Table Tennis (WTT) rankings, and has since been viewed as a serious contender for the gold medal at the Olympic Games in Paris.  Wang expressed sincere gratitude toward his coach Xiao Zhan and national team captain Ma Long for their help in his growth. He says the two pushed him to improve and served as positive role models.  Wang also revealed that his first goal at Paris 2024 will be to win the mixed doubles gold with Sun Yingsha. \\\"I want to give myself my pressure,\\\" he told CMG. \\\"When you have a clear target and a high requirement for yourself in practice, you can grow stronger and stronger.\\\"  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"